    <!-- Description (Blurb) -->

    <!-- description (optional, but highly encouraged) -->
    <!--   * optional                                                 -->
    <!--   * a sequence of HTML "p" elements, lists should be OK      -->
    <!--   * can contain simple markup, additional URLs               -->
    <!--   * a narrative description of the project's aims            -->
    <!--   * include distinctive features not possible above/below    -->
    <!--   * knowled, so brevity not required                         -->

    <description>
        <p><em>Mathématiques et algorithmes</em> is an open-access textbook written in French and
        designed for use in a one-semester introduction to algorithms from the mathematician's viewpoint.
        It only assumes basic knowledge in calculus as a prerequesite: good highschool students should understand this material.
        Also, this digital textbook is fueled with Python code and Sage interacts to help students experiment with algorithms.
        Topics covered include root finding, polynomial interpolation, numerical integration and number theory.</p>
    </description>

    <onesentence>
        Algorithms from the mathematician's viewpoint: an introductory course with Python code and Sage interacts.
    </onesentence>

